<subSubSection id="C3277AB9997AFF83FF77209AFC27FF06" pageId="3" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B822932997AFF83FF77209AFC27FF06" blockId="3.[160,1155,142,236]" pageId="3">
Endemic to Mexicoı reported from the following states: 
<collectingRegion id="49F9E7D0997AFF83FCBA209AFC1CFF20" box="[877,976,178,202]" country="Mexico" name="Guerrero" pageId="3">Guerrero</collectingRegion>
(Iguala de la Independencia and Zincauro) and 
<collectingRegion id="49F9E7D0997AFF83FDF220FCFDA1FF06" box="[549,621,212,236]" country="Mexico" name="Jalisco" pageId="3">Jalisco</collectingRegion>
(Sierra de Tuxcacuesco)ı 
<figureCitation id="130635B7997AFF83FC5E20FCFC2AFF06" box="[905,998,212,236]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[160,225,832,855]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,801]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[163,1153,142,801]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Map of distribution of the genus Devolana in Mexico." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3654593" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3654593/files/figure.png" pageId="3">Figure 4</figureCitation>
