</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3277AB9997AFF83FF772131FDDCFDE8" pageId="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B822932997AFF83FF772131FED8FED8" blockId="3.[160,1156,281,514]" box="[160,276,281,306]" pageId="3">
<emphasis id="B949F520997AFF83FF772131FED8FED8" bold="true" box="[160,276,281,306]" italics="true" pageId="3">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B822932997AFF83FF772114FDDCFDE8" blockId="3.[160,1156,281,514]" pageId="3">
<taxonomicName id="4C3D52B1997AFF83FF772114FEC0FEBE" authorityName="DeLongi" authorityYear="1967" box="[160,268,316,340]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Devolana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949F520997AFF83FF772114FEC0FEBE" box="[160,268,316,340]" italics="true" pageId="3">Devolana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from other similar genera of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D52B1997AFF83FC7F2114FBEFFEBE" authorityName="Van Duzee" authorityYear="1892" box="[936,1059,316,340]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Athysanini">Athysanini</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characteristics: (1) head very short with anterior and posterior margins of crown parallel; (2) face with arcuate black line extended from midline laterad through ocelli and along border of frontoclypeus; (3) pronotum with pair of large black spots; (4) pygofer without processes; and (5) aedeagus with a set of apical processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3277AB9997AFF83FF772206FCA9FA40" pageId="3" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B822932997AFF83FF772206FEFCFDAD" blockId="3.[160,1156,558,1450]" box="[160,304,558,583]" pageId="3">
<emphasis id="B949F520997AFF83FF772206FEFCFDAD" bold="true" box="[160,304,558,583]" italics="true" pageId="3">Morphology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B822932997AFF83FF77227AFD3EFB98" blockId="3.[160,1156,558,1450]" pageId="3">
Moderately robust leafhoppers with overall appearance yellowish with black spots on crown and pronotum. Crown roundedı paralleled to posterior margin. Transition of crown to face angledı shagreen. Ocellocular area parallel and wide. Ocelli slightly below margin of headı distance to adjacent eye approximately 2x ocellar diameter. Frontoclypeus wideı lateral frontal sutures reaching ocellusı fine setae laterad frontal suture. Anteclypeus widening apicallyı apex curved slightly surpassing natural curve of genae. Lorum subequal than anteclypeus near base. Genae incised laterad. Pronotum weakly produced mediallyı laterad margins carinateı yellowish with a symmetrical pair of large black spots and a paired diffuse palebrown line between them. Scutellum broad. Forewing macropterousı translucent with black-brown colour on vein-scheme or yellowish pigmentation near the base of clavusı appendix restricted to anal marginı apex roundedı apical and anteapical cells largeı Cs–Pcu crossvein absentı Pcu–A1 crossvein only presented in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D52B1997AFF83FF77243CFE9AFBC6" authorityName="Pinedo-Escatel and Aguilar-Perezi" authorityYear="2019" box="[160,342,1044,1068]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Devolana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuxcacuensis">
<emphasis id="B949F520997AFF83FF77243CFE9AFBC6" box="[160,342,1044,1068]" italics="true" pageId="3">D. tuxcacuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Front femur 
<collectionCode id="ED2CB1F7997AFF83FDDB243CFDF5FBC6" box="[524,569,1044,1068]" country="Australia" name="Australian Museum" pageId="3" type="Museum">AM</collectionCode>
1 near mid-height of apexı long; IC longı thin; row AV small. Front tibia dorsal macrosetal formula (AD+ 
<collectionCode id="ED2CB1F7997AFF83FC86241FFCB9FBA5" box="[849,885,1079,1103]" country="Netherlands" name="Dutch Plant Protection Service, Culture Collection of Plant Pathogenic Bacteria" pageId="3">PD</collectionCode>
) 1 + 4ı PV small stout setae. Hind femur macrosetal formula 2 + 2 + 1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B822932997AFF83FF172454FCA9FA40" blockId="3.[160,1156,558,1450]" pageId="3">Pygofer broadı shortı square or pointedı without processesı long and small stout macrosetae near apexı basolateral cleft present. Segment tenth smallı broadı wellsclerotised with membranous tip. Valve and subgenital plates free articulated to pygofer. Valve rounded and slightly produced. Subgenital plate trianguları uniseriate laterad with robust and fine setae. Connective Y-shapedı stem short. Style slenderı basal and preapical lobe weakly developed with setae on posterad marginı apophysis short and curved mesadı apex truncate. Aedeagus curved dorsadı aedeagal shaft with lateral flanges devolved or notı two or three pairs of apical processes. Aedeagal base without processes. Gonoduct sclerotised. Gonophore subapical on ventral surface.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3277AB9997AFF83FF7725FEFE2DF955" pageId="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B822932997AFF83FF7725FEFECAFA05" blockId="3.[160,1155,1494,1727]" box="[160,262,1494,1519]" pageId="3">
<emphasis id="B949F520997AFF83FF7725FEFECAFA05" bold="true" box="[160,262,1494,1519]" italics="true" pageId="3">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B822932997AFF83FF7725D2FE2DF955" blockId="3.[160,1155,1494,1727]" pageId="3">
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC54C3997AFF83FF7725D2FE89F9F8" author="DeLong DM" box="[160,325,1530,1554]" pageId="3" pagination="22 - 23" refId="ref4608" refString="DeLong DM. 1967. Devolana i new genus of Mexican Deltocephalinaei and a new species of Devolana (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Ohio J Sci. 67: 22 - 23." type="journal article" year="1967">DeLong (1967)</bibRefCitation>
compared this taxon to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D52B1997AFF83FD8F25D2FD75F9F8" authorityName="Ball" authorityYear="1929" box="[600,697,1530,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Exitianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949F520997AFF83FD8F25D2FD75F9F8" box="[600,697,1530,1554]" italics="true" pageId="3">Exitianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D52B1997AFF83FD2625D2FC92F9F8" authorityName="DeLong" authorityYear="1967" box="[753,862,1530,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Spinulana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949F520997AFF83FD2625D2FC92F9F8" box="[753,862,1530,1554]" italics="true" pageId="3">Spinulana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ı which differ by combinations of genital structures and external features. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D52B1997AFF83FD692634FCD3F9DE" authorityName="Ball" authorityYear="1929" box="[702,799,1564,1588]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Exitianus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949F520997AFF83FD692634FCD3F9DE" box="[702,799,1564,1588]" italics="true" pageId="3">Exitianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was included in tribe Chiasmini by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAC54C3997AFF83FF132617FDCBF9BD" author="Zahniser JNi Dietrich CH" box="[196,519,1599,1623]" pageId="3" pagination="1 - 211" refId="ref4923" refString="Zahniser JNi Dietrich CH. 2013. A review of the tribes of Deltocephalinae (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Cicadellidae). Eur J Taxon. 45: 1 - 211. doi: 10.5852 / ejt. 2013.45" type="journal article" year="2013">Zahniser and Dietrich (2013)</bibRefCitation>
; members of this tribe have a tapering or parallel-sided anteclypeus and an aedeagus hinged at the base. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D52B1997AFF83FD18264AFCF0F990" authorityName="DeLong" authorityYear="1967" box="[719,828,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Spinulana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949F520997AFF83FD18264AFCF0F990" box="[719,828,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="3">Spinulana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D52B1997AFF83FCA3264AFC10F990" authorityName="DeLongi" authorityYear="1967" box="[884,988,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Devolana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B949F520997AFF83FCA3264AFC10F990" box="[884,988,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="3">Devolana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ı both of which are currently placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3D52B1997AFF83FE4826ADFDD9F977" authorityName="Van Duzee" authorityYear="1892" box="[415,533,1669,1693]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Athysanini">Athysanini</taxonomicName>
differ in general body colour and in the structure of the male pygofer and aedeagus.
</paragraph>
